Durban - Police are investigating a case of murder after a body was found floating in a river in Oakford, near Verulam, this week. According to police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala, the man's arms and legs were bound. "He sustained a single gunshot wound to the head. The motive for the attack is unknown at this stage. The body has not been identified and the victim was wearing a blue denim jeans and dark-coloured jacket," she said. Reaction Unit SA director, Prem Balram, said their offices received a call from a resident informing them that they could see a body floating in the river, which leads into the Hazelmere Dam. "The victim's hands and legs were bound with a green and white ski-rope and he found was lying face down in the water. A pair of blue and white sandals were found next to a pool of blood on the river bank," he said. Police are appealing to anyone who may have information on the next of kin or who can identify the deceased to go or contact the Verulam SAPS on 032Â 541 5222 or call Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Daily News